This paper investigates the regularization effect of weight decay on neural networks, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning. The paper discusses the effect of weight decay on three optimization algorithms and various network architectures, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on the regularization effect of weight decay, cs.LG and cs.NE are the most likely sub-categories.
